               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Rubrication is executed in different tones of red: vivid red (e.g., fols. 3ra-4vb), vivid vermillion (e.g., fol. 15rb), strong vermillion (e.g., fol. 13rb); in some cases it differs even within one fol. (e.g., fols. 7r, 16r, 18r, 31r, 32v). It cannot be excluded that the rubrication was partly executed by a different hand.&#xD;
Nomina sacra and the name of the church Ṗäraqliṭos; incipit of Text I-1 (2 red lines alternating with black lines); incipit of Text I-2 (3 red lines above alternating with black lines, 2 red lines below) and its sections; incipit of Text I-3 and its numbers; words ʾǝsäggǝd, "I worship", mǝʿǝraf, "chapter" and its abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
Lacunae for (rubricated) names occasionally not filled (e.g. fols. 47ra, 98va, 120ra).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The miracles are numbered (except the 1st and 37th miracle).</note>
                  </msItem>
