                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work is written on the front board in yellow modern paint.&#xD;
- In the supplication formulas the säbʾa Betä Ṗäraqliṭos "people of Betä Ṗäraqliṭos" are most often mentioned, contrary to the donor Zä-Mikaʾel, who is mentioned only occasionally.&#xD;
- Numerous passages referring to the text are written in the upper margin, occasionally erased and re-written: e.g., fol. 61r.&#xD;
- Lacunae: fols. 66ra, 66vb.&#xD;
- Pen trial: fols. 6v, 125v.&#xD;
- Some erased or crossed out words/passages: e.g., fols. 20ra, 49rb, 53vb, 89va, 90rb, 91va [several lines], 95vb, 98rb 105va.&#xD;
- A few corrections written over erased words and passages: e.g., fols. 45vb, 75vb, 98ra, 100rb, 103va, 122va [19 lines].&#xD;
- Drawings of crosses: fol. 2r, 6v, in pen and ink.&#xD;
- Minor notes and writing exercises: fols. 2r, 6r.</item>
                     </list>
